<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id778bd3f5-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s425h"><num value="425h">§ 425h.</num><heading> Rules and regulations</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary of the Interior, subject to the approval of the President, shall have the power to make and shall make all needful rules and regulations for the care of the park, and for the establishment and marking of lines of battle and other historical features of the park.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id778bd3f6-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">(<ref href="/us/act/1927-02-14/ch127/s9">Feb. 14, 1927, ch. 127, § 9</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/44/1094">44 Stat. 1094</ref>; Ex. Ord. No. 6166, § 2, <date date="1933-06-10">June 10, 1933</date>; Ex. Ord. No. 6228, § 1, <date date="1933-07-28">July 28, 1933</date>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id778bd3f7-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="execDoc" id="id778bd3f8-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"><heading class="centered"><b>Executive Documents</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I85" topic="transferOfFunctions" id="id778bd3f9-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">
<heading class="centered smallCaps">Transfer of Functions</heading>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Transfer of administrative functions of park, see note set out under <ref href="/us/usc/t16/s425">section 425 of this title</ref>.</p>
</note>
</notes>
</section>
